LINUX exercise..

q1- add your custom alias
ans1. alias print='cat'

q2- create a soft link to a dir 
ans2. ln -s jquery j

q3- export env_vars MY_HOME and set it to /home/<userName>
ans3. export MY_HOME=/home/prashant

q4- Add a folder ~/myScripts to PATH
ans4. export PATH=$PATH:~/myScripts

q5- install cheese from apt-get
ans5. sudo apt-get install cheese

q6- find the occurances of "intelligrape" in the file a.txt
ans6. grep -cw intelligrape a.txt

q7- find number of files with the text "intelligrape" in folder "a1
ans7. grep -l "intelligrape" a/*.txt |wc -l

q8- find number of lines in a file
ans8. wc -l a.txt

q9- How to find file changed after a certain date
ans9.find /home/ -newermt "Feb 07"


q10- copy file from server - intelligrape@downloads.intelligrape.com - igdefault : The complete /home/intelligrape/downloads.intelligrape.com/
books folder.
ans10. scp meenakshi@10.1.0.103:/home/intelligrape/a.txt /home/prashant

q11- create a file using any command line editor(vim/pico) : c.txt, with the following text: "This is a sample file, welcome to intelligrape" and save the file and quit
ans11. vi c.txt(to save and exit :wq)

q12- copy file to server
ans12.scp /home/prashant/new.txt meenakshi@10.1.0.103:abc

q13- rename dir b1 to YOUR_NAME_B
ans13. mv b1 PS_B

q14- copy file from a.txt to /tmp/b.txt
ans14 cp a.txt /tmp/b.txt

q15- Try getting dump of selected table instead of the whole database
ans15.  mysqldump -u root -p data table1 > new_dump       //To create the dump
	
	mysql> source /home/prashant/new_dump.sql;	  //to restore table from the dump













